  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals are typically required to report suspicious transactions to designated authorities. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and documenting suspicious activities\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Conducting customer due diligence\n5. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nThe exact details depend on local laws and regulations.",
